<TITLE> Banglalink gets new CCO </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 30 (bdnews24.com)  Asher Yaqub Khan has been named the Chief Commercial Officer of Banglalink, the country's second largest mobile operator. The new appointment will be effective from September this year, Banglalink said in a press release on Thursday. Khan will replace Omer Rashid, who will be leaving for Canada to pursue other career interests, said Banglalink. "Khan brings with him a long path of 14 years of success in the fields of strategic and commercial expertise, 13 years of which is exclusively from the telecom industry" said the statement. Omer joined Banglalink as director of marketing on October 2004, becoming CCO in 2007. "Under his leadership Banglalink achieved several significant milestones  becoming the number two operator within a very short time and crossing the 10 million subscriber mark in only about 3 years of operations," said the company in its statement.
